    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-17T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-17T19:00:00-05:00" n="435"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.60/2–1748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-17T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 17, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>535. For <persName corresp="#p_DLW1">Douglas</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_SCE1">Saltzman</persName>.<note n="1" xml:id="d435fn1"
                        >Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DLW1">Douglas</persName> was the head of
                        the United States Delegation to the forthcoming London Conference on
                        Germany, and Assistant Secretary <persName corresp="#p_SCE1"
                            >Saltzman</persName> was a member.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Cabinet yesterday approved following recommendations re dismantling
                            program: <list>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Brit, French concurrence to be sought at London to continuance
                                    deliveries to Soviets only on strict barter basis. Failing such
                                    concurrence, position to be reconsidered by Cabinet.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Special group to be appointed by <persName corresp="#p_HWA1"
                                        >Harriman</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_KJA1"
                                        >Krug</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_ACP1"
                                        >Anderson</persName> to consider, with State and Army and in
                                    cooperation with technical staffs interested Congressional
                                    Committees, whether any plants scheduled for dismantling shld be
                                    retained for immediate production critical items. Substitutes to
                                    be sought for any plants recommended for retention. Brit, French
                                    cooperation such investigation to be sought London. Failing such
                                    cooperation, position to be reconsidered by Cabinet.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Reparation program except as affected by above recommendations
                                    to be continued unchanged and without delay.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Terms of reference<note n="2" xml:id="d435fn2">For the text of the
                                terms of reference referred to here, see <hi rend="italic"
                                    >supra</hi>.</note> of special group under (<hi rend="italic"
                                >b</hi>) above believed so defined that its activity should produce
                            no major change reparation program. It is hoped final decisions might be
                            reached within 6 to 8 weeks.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>In discussions with British and French their agreement should be
                            sought temporary suspension dismantling any plants their zones which are
                            designated by working group, emphasizing that this is without prejudice
                            their right final decision re permanent retention any particular plant.
                            Although working group may suggest categories in which substitutions
                            might be made, zonal Commander will designate any such substitute
                            plants. British and French should be assured that they will be kept
                            fully advised-all stages working group’s discussions and that State and
                            Army representatives will be in position guide these discussions as well
                            as conduct ail necessary contacts with British and French
                            representatives.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
